M a l e: Protarsomeres 1 to 3 weakly widened. Aedeagus (
Figs 48, 49
) 0.22-0.31 mm long, symmetrical, with basal bulb weakly sclerotized. Basal bulb very small. Articular processes large, prominent. Apical process of median lobe simple, long, at least twice as long as basal bulb, hardly inflexed, gradually narrowed or subparallel in dorsal view, subcylindrical and curved at tip in lateral view. Parameres narrow and long, weakly broadened apically in lateral view, almost evenly wide posterior bases in dorsal view, with membranous inner margin in basal third. Internal sac simple, with very narrow flagellum, spines and scale-like structures absent.
